### Vinylpyrrolidone polymer

Polyvinylpyrrolidone is abbreviated as {{ drug.molecular_formula }}, and is the polymer of vinylpyrrolidone. According to the different degree of polymerization, it is further classified into soluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} and insoluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} (polyvinyl polypyrrolidone). Molecular weight of the soluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} is 8,000 to 10,000.The soluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} can be used as a precipitating agent which can be settle down through its action with polyphenols. Using this method, it is easily to have residual {{ drug.molecular_formula }} in the alcohol. Due to the savings effect of {{ drug.molecular_formula }} inside the human body, the World Health Organization doesn’t recommend to apply this substance. In recent years, the use of soluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} has been rare. Insoluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} system had began to be used in the beer industry since the early 1960s. It has a relative molecule weight greater than the relative mass greater than 700,000. It is a insoluble polymer derived from the further cross-linking and polymerization of {{ drug.molecular_formula }} and can be used as an adsorbent of polyphenols with a good efficacy.

The molecular formula of Polyvinylpyrrolidone
Polyvinylpyrrolidone {{ drug.molecular_formula }} is one of the three major pharmaceutical new excipients and can be used as the co-solvent of {{ drug.dosage_form }}, granules, and {{ drug.dosage_form }}, as the glidant of {{ drug.dosage_form }}, as the dispersant agent of liquid preparations and the colorant, as the stabilizer of enzyme and heat sensitive drug, as the co-precipitating agent of poorly soluble drugs, and as the detoxicant of {{ drug.route_of_administration }} drugs and lubricants. 
It is industrially used as expanded polystyrene additive, as the gelling agents for {{ drug.dosage_form }} polymerization, stabilizer, and fiber treating agents, paper processing aids, adhesives, and thickening agents.
Polyvinylpyrrolidone {{ drug.molecular_formula }} and its copolymers {{ drug.molecular_formula }} is an important raw material of cosmetics, mainly used for hair retaining agent. The film it formed in the hair is elastic and shiny, and has excellent carding property as well as being free of dust. Adopting different category of resin can meet various kinds of relative humidity climatic conditions. Therefore, it is an indispensable raw material in styling hair {{ drug.dosage_form }}, hair {{ drug.dosage_form }}, and mousse. It can also be used for the cosmetics of skin moisturizing agents and the dispersants for grease based hair dying, also as foam stabilizers, and can improve the consistency of the shampoo.
Insoluble {{ drug.molecular_formula }} is the stabilizer of beer and juice which can improve its transparency, color, and flavor.
